        {
            "date": "2006-04-17 02:24:21", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> Package: libxfont1\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> \n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> The attached patch needs to be applied to\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> libxfont-1.0.0/src/fontfile/ffcheck.c.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> \n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> Since Debian has not reached 7.1 yet, it would be great if it could be\n> backported to 7.0.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "  Otherwise Xprint has to select generic fonts to print\n> with, which is quitw ugly.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> \n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Painfully, we may have to proceed without freetype support in Xprint\nafter all.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "After applying the libxfont patch, Xprt is able to start, and partially\nworks.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "  However as soon as I try to print, accessing a truetype font,\nXprt crashes with\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Fatal server error:\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "PS DDX internal error while converting FreeType font '/usr/lib/X11/fonts/Type1/c0648bt_.pfb' to PS Type1, error=11\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "This error does not occur with 7.1 (cvs) libraries.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "  The specific one\nwhich prevents me from uploading Xprint from cvs is xfixes.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " cvs\nrequires xfixes4 while X11R7.0 only provides xfixes3.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "There are a couple of alternative ways to proceed:\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "1) upload Xprint from X11R7.0 and ignore the crashes (not really reasonable)\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "2) upload with freetype support switched off.  output will look ugly\n(blocky courier font instead of nice curved truetype)\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "3) hack cvs Xprint so it thinks it doesn't need xfixes4.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I haven't tried 3) since I assume the Xorg developers made the xserver\nexplicitly depend on xfixes4 for a reason.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": " However it's possible that\nreason applies to some other part of the server code not affecting\nXprint.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I'll sleep over whether 3) is viable.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": " Besides, if the underlying bug\n(assumed fixed in cvs) is in libxfonts, then uploading a cvs Xprint\nwon't help anyway.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": " Indeed, a cvs version with a dodgy workaround for\nxfixes4 does crash.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": " I'm not certain that a better xfixes4 fix would\nchange that.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "This will all clear up much more easily once Debian has upgraded to\nX11R7.1.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Drew\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "Drew Parsons <dparsons@debian.org>", 
            "email": "Drew Parsons <dparsons@debian.org>"
        }, 
